   350	- 2026-04-26 [orchestration][parent-commit] **When a worker produces a verifiably-green diff but fails at a tooling step (sandbox / network / auth), parent committing the worker's diff directly is the right escape hatch — re-launching is wasted token spend.** cov-redact slice: worker reported `OFFLINE-FAIL commit blocked by sandbox Git lock` with full evidence (28 tests pass, redact.py 100% cov, mypy clean, ruff check clean, full diff in worktree). Parent re-ran the green-check suite from a parent shell to verify (passed), then committed directly. Saves a full re-launch (~135k tokens). Eligibility test: (1) worker's claim of green-checks must be re-verifiable from parent without re-running the worker's logic; (2) the diff must be what was contractually expected (no scope creep); (3) the failure mode must be a tooling layer, not a logic-or-test failure. If any of those don't hold, re-launch. Pattern: workers are deliverable-producers, parent is committer-of-record; the structural separation already supports this escape hatch — use it.
