   352	- 2026-04-26 [gh-install][bundle-layout] **Copying just the `bin/gh` binary out of a `gh_<ver>_macOS_arm64/` release tarball produces a binary that macOS kills with SIGKILL (exit 137) on every invocation, despite the codesign being intact and the embedded signature passing `codesign -dvv`.** Working signature: `Developer ID Application: GitHub (VEKTX9H2N7)`, hardened runtime, valid Apple cert chain. Yet a bare `cp gh_*/bin/gh ~/.local/bin/gh && ~/.local/bin/gh --version` reproducibly exit-137s. Fix: copy the FULL bundle (with `share/man/`, `share/zsh/`, etc. siblings) to `~/.local/share/gh/`, then `ln -sf ~/.local/share/gh/bin/gh ~/.local/bin/gh`. Symlinked binary works because gatekeeper / hardened-runtime checks evaluate the bundle layout, not just the binary itself. Pattern: any signed CLI that ships in a multi-directory bundle on macOS should be installed by preserving the bundle layout + symlinking the entry-point — never by lifting the binary out. (Verified for gh v2.91.0 from official `cli/cli` release; same pattern likely applies to other Mach-O CLIs with associated `share/` resources.)
