   365	- 2026-04-26 [orchestration][under-utilisation] **Defensible per-task reasons can hide aggregate parent-overload — audit the worker-runs-per-sprint ratio, not just per-task fit.** Sprints 7h-4 → 7h-8 ran 8 PRs, 4 doc reconciles, 1 codex/* triage, 1 PAT rotation, 1 branch-stack-pollution recovery, 5 daybook syncs, full README+CHANGELOG+RECONCILIATION+V1_GA reconcile — and ZERO codex worker runs. Each individual decision to skip codex was defensible (PR work needs `gh` PAT decisions; doc reconcile is mostly summarising what parent just did). The aggregate was parent-overload; ~3h of operator time, 0 worker time. Pattern: at every sprint boundary, ask "did I run a worker this sprint?" — if no, name why; if the answer is "I did everything synchronously myself", the next sprint must queue at least one. Workers being expensive to scope is a reason to invest in prefabs (`PREFAB_*.md`), not a reason to keep doing it parent-only.
