## Tenant-side shared state (per-profile-collision-risk)
| Resource | Shared by N profiles? | Collision risk | Isolation strategy |
|----------|-----------------------|----------------|--------------------|
| Gateway `Lab GW Rocky` | yes | low (read-mostly) | none needed |
| Admin Commander session | yes (admin login is global) | HIGH if shared `~/.keeper/` | per-profile `KEEPER_CONFIG=/path/to/profile-N/.keeper-config.json` env var |
| testuser session | per-profile by definition | none | already isolated |
| Shared folder | per-profile | none | already isolated |
| KSM app | per-profile | none | already isolated |
| Marker channel | per-profile | none | already isolated |
| Audit alerts / SCIM endpoints | tenant-global | medium | optionally per-profile node |
| Tenant write throttle | yes (Commander API rate limits) | medium | document N≤3 as default |

## Process-side shared state
| Resource | Risk | Mitigation |
|----------|------|------------|
| `keeper` CLI in subprocess | shared `~/.keeper/` config; race on `params.json` rewrite | each profile MUST set `KEEPER_CONFIG=<unique path>` (verify Commander honours; cite Commander source if available) |
| pytest cache | benign | per-profile `--profile` token in artifact paths |
| `/tmp/dsk-*` temp files | benign if PID-suffixed | smoke already PID-suffixes; confirm |

## Recommended concurrency cap
- N=2 in dev; N=3 in CI; N>3 only with maintainer approval (tenant rate-limit prudence).
- Per-profile config directory must be **physically copied** before first run (Commander rewrites in place).

## Lock design (if needed)
- File lock at `<repo>/.dsk-smoke-tenant.<tenant>.lock`?
- Argument: keep per-tenant lock OPEN-by-default (no file lock) but document the cap. Rationale: file locks add complexity; the per-profile config-dir isolation is the real fix.

## Live-proof rule update proposal
- Old: "one writer per tenant".
- New (proposed): "one writer per profile per tenant; profiles must use disjoint per-profile `KEEPER_CONFIG` directories and disjoint marker channels". 
- PARENT-DECIDE: accept rule update OR keep stricter rule + queue.

