   111	
   112	| Resource | Risk | Mitigation |
   113	|---|---|---|
   114	| `keeper` CLI config | Commander CLI itself honors `--config` and `KEEPER_CONFIG_FILE`, not `KEEPER_CONFIG` directly ([__main__.py](/Users/martin/Library/Python/3.14/lib/python/site-packages/keepercommander/__main__.py:40), [__main__.py](/Users/martin/Library/Python/3.14/lib/python/site-packages/keepercommander/__main__.py:153)). | For raw `keeper`, pass `--config <profile-config>` or set `KEEPER_CONFIG_FILE`. For SDK provider, `KEEPER_CONFIG` is translated into `--config` ([commander_cli.py](</Users/martin/Downloads/Cursor tests/declarative-sdk-for-k/keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:176>), [commander_cli.py](</Users/martin/Downloads/Cursor tests/declarative-sdk-for-k/keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:1657>)). |
