   121	
   122	## Commander Config Finding
   123	
   124	`KEEPER_CONFIG` is honored by this SDK, not by raw Commander CLI. `CommanderCliProvider` reads `KEEPER_CONFIG` and appends `--config <path>` for subprocess calls. `EnvLoginHelper` also reads `KEEPER_CONFIG` for in-process login. Raw `keeper` uses `--config` or `KEEPER_CONFIG_FILE`; otherwise it falls back to default `.keeper` storage. Therefore two raw `keeper` invocations sharing defaults can collide.
   125	
   126	The config must be physically copied per profile before first run because Commander rewrites it in place and stores the cache DB beside it.
   127	
   128	## Recommended Concurrency Cap
   129	
   130	- Now: keep live proof serial per tenant.
   131	- After profile parameterization + config isolation + lock/proof: N=2 in dev, N=3 in CI.
   132	- N>3 requires maintainer approval because tenant throttle and enterprise-global side effects are unmeasured.
   133	
   134	## Lock Design
   135	
   136	Do not add a repo-wide per-tenant lock as the first move. It would preserve today’s bottleneck while hiding the real requirement: per-profile config, user, shared folder, KSM app, marker channel, and project name isolation.
   137	
   138	Before CI parallelism, add a lightweight code-level guard that refuses `--parallel-profile` unless a unique config path and unique resource prefix are present. A file lock can then be per profile, e.g. `.dsk-smoke-profile.<tenant>.<profile>.lock`, not one tenant-wide lock.
   139	
   140	## Live-proof rule update proposal
   141	
   142	Old rule: one live session / writer lane per tenant ([README.md](</Users/martin/Downloads/Cursor tests/declarative-sdk-for-k/docs/live-proof/README.md:31>)); L1 remains serial per tenant ([README.md](</Users/martin/Downloads/Cursor tests/declarative-sdk-for-k/docs/live-proof/README.md:97>).
   143	
   144	Proposed rule after fixes: “one writer per profile per tenant; profiles must use disjoint Commander config paths, test users, shared folders, KSM apps, marker channels, and project names.”
   145	
   146	PARENT-DECIDE: keep stricter rule until the smoke harness is parameterized and `CommanderCliProvider` has an explicit session-isolation guard.
