   187	
   188	## Commander Config Finding
   189	
   190	`KEEPER_CONFIG` is honored by this SDK, not by raw Commander CLI. `CommanderCliProvider` reads `KEEPER_CONFIG` and appends `--config <path>` for subprocess calls. `EnvLoginHelper` also reads `KEEPER_CONFIG` for in-process login. Raw `keeper` uses `--config` or `KEEPER_CONFIG_FILE`; otherwise it falls back to default `.keeper` storage. Therefore two raw `keeper` invocations sharing defaults can collide.
   191	
   192	The config must be physically copied per profile before first run because Commander rewrites it in place and stores the cache DB beside it.
   193	
   194	## Recommended Concurrency Cap
   195	
   196	- Now: keep live proof serial per tenant.
   197	- After profile parameterization + config isolation + lock/proof: N=2 in dev, N=3 in CI.
   198	- N>3 requires maintainer approval because tenant throttle and enterprise-global side effects are unmeasured.
   199	
   200	## Lock Design
   201	
   202	Do not add a repo-wide per-tenant lock as the first move. It would preserve today’s bottleneck while hiding the real requirement: per-profile config, user, shared folder, KSM app, marker channel, and project name isolation.
   203	
   204	Before CI parallelism, add a lightweight code-level guard that refuses `--parallel-profile` unless a unique config path and unique resource prefix are present. A file lock can then be per profile, e.g. `.dsk-smoke-profile.<tenant>.<profile>.lock`, not one tenant-wide lock.
   205	
   206	## Live-proof rule update proposal
   207	
   208	Old rule: one live session / writer lane per tenant ([README.md](</Users/martin/Downloads/Cursor tests/declarative-sdk-for-k/docs/live-proof/README.md:31>)); L1 remains serial per tenant ([README.md](</Users/martin/Downloads/Cursor tests/declarative-sdk-for-k/docs/live-proof/README.md:97>).
   209	
   210	Proposed rule after fixes: “one writer per profile per tenant; profiles must use disjoint Commander config paths, test users, shared folders, KSM apps, marker channels, and project names.”
   211	
   212	PARENT-DECIDE: keep stricter rule until the smoke harness is parameterized and `CommanderCliProvider` has an explicit session-isolation guard.
