# Concurrency guard — implementation design (CDX-S3, 2026-04-27T04:05:14Z)

## Evidence Baseline
- Current `smoke.py` argparse has `--teardown`, `--keep-records`, `--log-level`, `--scenario`, and `--login-helper`; no profile/parallel flag exists in this snapshot (`scripts/smoke/smoke.py:679-713`).
- `main()` parses args, sets the active scenario, then calls `run_smoke()` once (`scripts/smoke/smoke.py:716-734`).
- Current live flow logs in admin, ensures test identity, refreshes admin login, provisions sandbox, then pre-cleans records (`scripts/smoke/smoke.py:115-147`).
- Current shared names are constants: project `sdk-smoke-testuser2` (`scripts/smoke/smoke.py:43`), shared folder `SDK Test (ephemeral)` and app `SDK Test KSM` (`scripts/smoke/sandbox.py:21-22`).
- Current admin config fallback is the lab default `keeper-vault-rbi-pam-testenv/commander-config.json` (`scripts/smoke/identity.py:27-31`, `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:168-170`).
- Current SDK subprocess env is forced to `KEEPER_CONFIG=admin_config_path` after bootstrap (`scripts/smoke/smoke.py:175-178`).
- `CommanderCliProvider` also reads `KEEPER_CONFIG` into `self._config` and caches `KeeperParams` per provider instance (`keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:176-188`).
- Provider subprocesses add `--config <path>` when `self._config` is set (`keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:1657-1662`).
- `EnvLoginHelper` copies `KEEPER_CONFIG` into `config_path` and passes it into Commander login (`keeper_sdk/auth/helper.py:224-246`).
- Provider discover has vault filtering and PAM synthetic/remote-browser enrichment branches (`keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:147-157`, `keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:207-262`).
- Vault apply is selected from `apply_plan()` and requires a folder UID before mutating (`keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:491-493`, `keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:786-806`).
- The provider session cache is instance-local via `_keeper_params`; `_get_keeper_params()` returns that cache and has no cross-process lock surface (`keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:182-188`, `keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:1973-1981`).
- Current live-proof docs require one writer lane per tenant and serial L1 per tenant (`docs/live-proof/README.md:31-33`, `docs/live-proof/README.md:97-101`).

## Public Surface
- New CLI flag on `scripts/smoke/smoke.py`: `--parallel-profile`, boolean, default `false`.
- Valid only after S1 lands `--profile`; current argparse has no `--profile`, so S1 is a hard dependency (`scripts/smoke/smoke.py:679-713`).
- When false, preserve current behavior: no lock creation, same single `run_smoke()` path (`scripts/smoke/smoke.py:716-734`).
- When true, create one profile-scoped lock before the first tenant mutation.
- Lock filename: `.dsk-smoke-<tenant>-<profile_id>.lock`.
- Default full path: `<repo-root>/.dsk-smoke-locks/.dsk-smoke-<tenant>-<profile_id>.lock`.
- This uses the requested filename stem while satisfying the lock-directory requirement.
- `tenant` in the filename is a filesystem-safe normalized FQDN, not raw user input.

## Lock File Format
- JSON object, written atomically with exclusive create.
- `pid`: int.
- `started_at`: UTC ISO string.
- `tenant_fqdn`: str.
- `profile_id`: str.
- `admin_commander_config`: str, absolute physical path.
- `sf_title`: str.
- `ksm_app_name`: str.
- `project_name`: str.
- Optional after S1 if exposed: `testuser_email`: str.
- Do not put secrets, tokens, passwords, TOTP values, config JSON, or UIDs in the lock.

## Placement In Flow
- Run local profile/env preflight immediately after parsing args.
- Resolve tenant after `admin_login()` because current smoke receives `admin_params` there (`scripts/smoke/smoke.py:115-124`).
- Acquire the lock after admin login and before `ensure_sdktest_identity()`.
- Reason: identity bootstrap can mutate tenant/user state and write Commander config (`scripts/smoke/identity.py:407-416`).
- Also acquire before sandbox provisioning and pre-clean (`scripts/smoke/smoke.py:131-147`).
- Store the lock path in `state`.
- Release the lock unconditionally in `main()`’s `finally`, after any cleanup, because current cleanup already lives there (`scripts/smoke/smoke.py:751-787`).
- Also register an `atexit` release handler as a best-effort backup.
- Do not release before project cleanup; current success path removes project tree near the end (`scripts/smoke/smoke.py:325-328`).

## Refusal Conditions
- Refuse if `--parallel-profile` is set but `--profile` is missing or `default`.
- Refuse if any active lock has the same physical `admin_commander_config` as the current profile.
- Refuse if any two active lock files already collide on `admin_commander_config`; this means the lock dir is inconsistent.
- Refuse if any active lock collides with the current profile on `sf_title`, `ksm_app_name`, or `project_name`.
- Refuse if any two active lock files already collide on those resource names.
- Refuse if the current profile’s `admin_commander_config` is the workspace default lab config (`scripts/smoke/identity.py:27-31`, `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:168-170`).
- Refuse if `KEEPER_CONFIG` is set and differs from the profile’s `admin_commander_config`.
- The env mismatch matters because both provider and env-helper paths consume `KEEPER_CONFIG` (`keeper_sdk/providers/commander_cli.py:176`, `keeper_sdk/auth/helper.py:224-246`).

## Tenant Identification
- Prefer `admin_params.config["server"]` after admin login.
- Fallback order: `KEEPER_SERVER`, then `identity.KEEPER_SERVER`.
- `identity.KEEPER_SERVER` currently defaults to `keepersecurity.com` (`scripts/smoke/identity.py:33`).
- `KeeperParams` config/server construction in the local identity helper shows the expected config shape (`scripts/smoke/identity.py:132-137`).
- Keep locks per tenant so two tenants on the same machine do not block each other.

## Lock Directory
- Default lock dir: `<repo-root>/.dsk-smoke-locks/`.
- `ROOT` already exists in `smoke.py` and points at repo root (`scripts/smoke/smoke.py:17`).
- Override with `DSK_SMOKE_LOCK_DIR`.
- Add `.dsk-smoke-locks/` to `.gitignore` near the existing live-smoke/operator artifact block (`.gitignore:22-32`).
- If lock-dir creation or lock-file write fails, refuse before tenant mutation.

## Failure Modes
- Stale lock with PID no longer running: remove it, warn, then proceed.
- Stale lock with PID alive and `started_at` older than 24h: refuse with “stuck lock” message and require operator removal.
- Active overlapping lock younger than 24h: refuse with the colliding field and lock path.
- Corrupt JSON lock: refuse, print path, do not guess.
- Future timestamp beyond small clock-skew tolerance: refuse as corrupt/stuck.
- Atomic create collision: re-scan lock dir once, then refuse with the active lock details.

## Non-goals
- Do not change SDK marker manager per profile.
- `MANAGER_NAME` is core ownership state (`keeper_sdk/core/metadata.py:27`).
- Diff treats other managers as conflicts and delete filtering only touches matching manager markers (`keeper_sdk/core/diff.py:441-451`, `keeper_sdk/core/diff.py:527-535`).
- Isolation must come from profile resource scope, not marker identity.

## Tests (Offline)
- `test_smoke_parallel_guard_refuses_default_profile.py`: parse `--parallel-profile --profile default`; expect preflight refusal.
- `test_smoke_parallel_guard_detects_config_collision.py`: temp lock dir, fake active lock with matching `admin_commander_config`; expect refusal.
- `test_smoke_parallel_guard_releases_on_exit.py`: acquire/release via fake profile state; lock file gone.
- `test_smoke_parallel_guard_recovers_stale_pid.py`: fake bogus PID lock; expect proceed plus warning.
- Put these near existing smoke-arg tests, which already import `smoke._parse_args()` offline (`tests/test_smoke_args.py:9-22`).
- Use monkeypatch/temp-path style already present in smoke tests (`tests/test_smoke_args.py:42-54`).

## LOC Estimate
- About 100 LOC production: profile lock dataclass/dict builder, lock-dir scan, stale-PID handling, collision checks, argparse wiring, release hook.
- About 80 LOC tests across the four offline cases.

## Dependencies
- S1 multi-profile refactor must merge first because current smoke has only shared constants and no profile arg (`scripts/smoke/smoke.py:39-45`, `scripts/smoke/smoke.py:679-713`).
- Daybook already orders multi-profile before concurrency guard (`/Users/martin/Downloads/JOURNAL.md:1703-1708`).
- No tenant-side changes.
- No live Commander call should be added for the guard except the existing admin login needed to resolve tenant.

## Live-proof Rule Update
- Replace current rule “one live session / writer lane per tenant at a time” (`docs/live-proof/README.md:31-33`).
- Also update the parallel orchestration sentence that says L1 is serial per tenant (`docs/live-proof/README.md:97-101`).
- New text: “one writer per profile per tenant; profiles must use disjoint Commander config paths, test users, shared folders, KSM apps, and project names. The smoke harness enforces this via per-profile lock files when `--parallel-profile` is set.”

## CANDIDATE LESSON
- 2026-04-27 [smoke][lock-design] Per-profile live-smoke parallelism needs an explicit local lock that proves disjoint Commander config and resource names before the first tenant mutation; profile isolation is an enforced preflight, not a convention.
